1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with event-based camera localization, which is a subfield of computer vision. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses tracking the pose of a camera in a known environment, which is relevant to robotics. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper uses a Bayesian filtering framework, which is a machine learning technique. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper proposes a probabilistic generative event model, which is a common technique in AI. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with tracking the motion of a camera, which is relevant to systems and control.
